# benchmarks/results/ is v0.11-era output. Kept on the legacy/v0.11.0 tag;
# rebuild/v2 ignores everything except the headline files referenced from
# memory entries / REBUILD_PLAN. Phase 7 regenerates fresh result files
# against the v2.0 default recipe and adds them to the keep list explicitly.
benchmarks/results/**
# Headline keepers (alphabetical within each subdir). Each file is the
# evidence backstop for a memory entry or a documented baseline.
!benchmarks/results/beir/
!benchmarks/results/beir/pipeline_*_honest_e5_raw_v1.json
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/aggregate_5beir_horizon1_v239.json
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/aggregate_5beir_qwen3_8b_v1.json
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/baseline_qwen3_8b_v1/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/baseline_qwen3_8b_v1/**
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/baseline_qwen3_8b_v1_meanpool_broken/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/baseline_qwen3_8b_v1_meanpool_broken/**
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/qwen3_8b_fullstack_v1/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/qwen3_8b_fullstack_v1/**
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/stage1_v1/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/stage1_v1/**
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/ws3_291_parity/
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/ws3_291_parity/aggregate_ws3_291_parity_5beir.json
!benchmarks/results/locomo/
!benchmarks/results/locomo/phase1_smoke_conv1_v3.json
!benchmarks/results/locomo/phase2_5_cartridge_e5_cascade_all10.json
!benchmarks/results/locomo/phase2_cartridge_e5_all10.json
!benchmarks/results/locomo/phase2_cartridge_e5_all10_sonnet_judge.json
# v2.0-stack LoCoMo retrieval recall (gte-mb 768d, FAISS HNSW). 1982 QAs
# across 10 conversations; replaces v0.11 cartridge-baseline 68.2%
# (different metric, same dataset).
!benchmarks/results/locomo/locomo_v2_retrieval.json
# Per-feature ablation smokes (2026-04-23) — kept as the audit trail for
# project_locomo_feature_transfer.md memory claims.
!benchmarks/results/locomo/smoke/
!benchmarks/results/locomo/smoke/**
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/v14_full500_800.json
# v2.0-stack LongMemEval retrieval (gte-mb 768d base band, 500 instances).
# MRR 0.936; per-question-type breakdown in JSON.
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/longmemeval_v2_retrieval.json
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/kaggle_v15_phase1_e5/
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/kaggle_v15_phase1_e5/**
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/runpod_v15_bge/
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/runpod_v15_bge/**
# Audit evidence (Phase 1 #14): FAISS-vs-hnswlib lock + efS=128 calibration.
!benchmarks/results/ann_audit_04.json
# Phase 1 #15 evidence: locked BEIR-5 floor for v2.0 base 768d gte-mb.
# Source-of-truth backstop for docs/internal/BENCHMARK_GATE.md.
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/v2_floor_gte_mb_base_768d.json
# v2.0-stack BEIR-5 encoder comparison (gte-mb vs BGE-large vs E5-large vs
# Qwen3-4B). Same retrieval pipeline; replaces v0.11-era cross-encoder
# comparisons that ran on different chunkers and ANN configs.
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/beir5_encoder_comparison_v1.json
# Audit 4 / OPTIMISE.md headline win — Fabric optimised probe (62,953 passages,
# +0.032 R@5, $8.16 / ~50 min Kaggle T4). Source-of-truth for the optimise
# three-row table in OPTIMISE.md, BENCHMARKS.md, README.md.
!benchmarks/results/optimised/
!benchmarks/results/optimised/fabric_probe_v1.json
# Bench 7 — BEIR fiqa optimise probe (Δ -0.042 nDCG@10, $2.47 / ~20 min T4).
# Public-corpus negative result that falsified the predicted-positive
# hypothesis; ships alongside Fabric in the OPTIMISE.md three-row table.
!benchmarks/results/optimised/beir_fiqa_probe_v1.json
# User-facing benchmark results from `python -m benchmarks.user_bench.<n>.run`.
# hallucination_fabric_v3.json is the headline bench-2 result (Microsoft
# Fabric corpus, 13× hallucination reduction vs LLM-only).
!benchmarks/results/user_bench/
!benchmarks/results/user_bench/*.json
# Final-pattern wins: even inside allow-listed dirs, never track logs / npy
# / jsonl / sweep transcripts. Keep only the headline JSON files.
benchmarks/results/**/*.log
benchmarks/results/**/*.npy
benchmarks/results/**/*.jsonl
benchmarks/results/**/sweep*.json
# Specific run logs paired with headline results — kept as audit evidence
# alongside the benchmark JSONs they validate.
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/stage1_v1/driver.log
!benchmarks/results/beir/new_arch/stage1_v1/driver_v2.log
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/kaggle_v15_phase1_e5/rlat-longmemeval-v15-phase1-e5.log
!benchmarks/results/longmemeval/runpod_v15_bge/run.log

